President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New Jersey and ordered Federal assistance to help with recovery efforts following a severe winter storm and snowstorm that occurred from March 6 to March 7, 2018. Federal funding will be available to the State, eligible local governments, and certain private nonprofit organizations for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in the counties of Bergen, Essex, Morris, Passaic, and Somerset. Snow removal funding will also be available for a continuous 48-hour period in Bergen and Morris counties. Additionally, there will be cost-sharing for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Lai Sun Yee has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made if requested by the State and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.